# Status file

## Overview

A status file provides a snap-shot of the model at a given time-step. This is useful for debugging, for rendering the model, and for investigating the behavior of molecules in specific regions of the lattice.

The status file complements and augments the summary information that is stored in the [result file](../results/results.html).

Each status file takes time to write to disc. Consequently, FiberCpp does not write status files unless they are requested for a given simulation. See [options](../options/options.html) for information about how to generate status files for specific time-steps.

## Details

Status files are saved in [JSON format](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JSON).

[Click here for an example file](example_status_file.json)

Details about each section are provided below.

### hs_data

The `hs_data` section provides high-level information about the snap-shot.

````
"hs_data":
{
	"hs_id": 0,
	"time": 0.0401,
	"hs_length": 1200,
	"hs_force": 76762,
	"pCa": 4.5,
	"m_nodes_per_thick_filament": 54,
	"a_nodes_per_thin_filament": 189,
	"cb_extensions": [0, 0, 5]
}
````

| Key | Comment |
| ---- | ---- |
| hs_id | the index of the half-sarcomere, 0 for a single half-sarcomere simulation |
| time | time in seconds for the snap-shot |
| hs_length | the half-sarcomere length in nm |
| pCa | the Ca<sup>2+</sup> concentration |
| m_nodes_per_thick_filament | the number of myosin nodes per thick filament |
| a_nodes_per_thin_filament | the number of actin nodes per thin filament |
| cb_extensions | an array holding the power-stroke distances for each myosin state |

### titin

The `titin` section provides information about the titin component.

````
"titin":
{
	"t_k_stiff": 0.000015,
	"t_slack_length": 0.000000,
	"t_attach_a_node": 21,
	"t_attach_m_node": 54
}
````

| Key | Comment |
| ---- | ---- |
| t_k_stiff | the stiffness of titin links (N m<sup>-1</sup>) |
| t_slack_length | the slack length of titin in nm |
| t_attach_a_node | the node on actin to which titin attaches |
| t_attach_m_node | the node on myosin to which titin attaches |

| Key | Comment |
| ---- | ---- |
| thick_id | the thick filament index |
| m_y | the y coordinate of the filament |
| m_z | the z coordinate of the filament |
| m_no_of_cbs | the number of myosin heads on each filament |
| m_k_stiff | the stiffness of inter-node links in N m<sup>-1</sup> |
| m_k_cb | the stiffness of an actin-myosin link in N m<sup>-1</sup>|
| c_k_stiff | the stiffness of an actin-myosin-binding protein-C link in N m<sup>-1</sup> |
| m_inter_crown_rest_length | the distance between myosion crowns at zero force |
| m_cbs_per_node | the number of myosin heads per node |
| m_lambda | the distance between the M-line and the start of the bare zone |
| c_no_of_pcs | the number of myosin binding protein-C molecules per filament |
| nearest_actin_filaments | the indices of the nearest actin filaments, starting at 12 o-clock and proceeeding clock-wise |
| cb_x | the x position in nm of each myosin head |
| cb_angle | the angle in degrees at which each head protudes |
| cb_state | the state number of each head |
| cb_bound_to_a_f | the index of the actin filament each head is bound to, -1 means not bound |
| cb_bound_to_a_n | the index of the binding site each head is bound to, -1 means not bound |
| cb_nearest_a_f | the index of the actin filament nearest to the head |
| cb_nearest_a_n[x_0] | the index of the binding site nearest to the head |
| cb_nearest_a_n_states[x_0] | the state of the binding site nearest to the head |
| cb_nearest_bs_angle_diff[x_0] | the angle between the head and the nearest binding site |
| cb_controlling_pc_index | the index of the myosin binding protein-C molecule controlling the myosin head, -1 means no influencing molecule |
| node_forces | the force at each head |
| pc_node_index | the thick filament node at which each myosin binding protein-C is positioned |
| pc_angle | the angle in degrees at which each myosin binding protein C protrudes |
| pc_state | the state number of each myosin binding protein-C |
| pc_iso | the isotype of each myosin binding protein-C |
| pc_bound_to_a_f | the index of the actin filament each myosin binding protein-C is bound to, -1 means not bound |
| pc_bound_to_a_n | the index of the binding site each myosin binding protein-C is bound to, -1 means not bound |
| pc_nearest_a_f | the index of the actin filament nearest to each myosin binding protein-C |
| pc_nearest_a_n[x_0] | the index of the binding site nearest to each myosin binding protein-C |
| pc_nearest_a_n_states[x_0] | the state of the binding site nearest to each myosin binding protein-C |
| pc_nearest_bs_angle_diff[x_0] | the angle between the myosin binding protein-C and the nearest binding site |

| Key | Comment |
| ---- | ---- |
| thin_id | the thin filament index |
| a_y | the y coordinate of the filament |
| a_z | the z coordinate of the filament |
| a_no_of_bs | the number of binding sites on each filament |
| a_bs_per_node | the number of binding sites per node |
| a_k_stiff | the stiffness of an inter-node link in N m<sup>-1</sup>|
| a_inter_bs_rest_length | the distance between binding sites in nm at zero force |
| bs_x | the x position in nm of each binding site |
| bs_angle | the angle in degrees at which each binding site protudes |
| bs_unit | the regulatory unit to which the binding site belongs |
| bs_state | the state number of each binding site |
| bs_isoform | the isoform number of each binding site |
| unit_status | the status of each regulatory unit |
| bound_to_m_f | the index of the thick filament to which the binding site is linked, -1 means not bound |
| bound_to_m_n | the index of the head to which the binding site is linked, -1 means not bound |
| bound_to_m_type | the state number of the myosin link, 0 means not attached |
